âš¡ 2. Date/Time Methods in JavaScript (Most Used in Projects)

---------------------------------------------------------------------->
âœ… Creating Dates

new Date()                  // current date & time
new Date("2025-09-06")      // from string
new Date(2025, 8, 6, 10, 30) // year, month(0-based), day, hr, min
Date.now()                  // timestamp in ms
 
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------->

âœ… Getting Values

getFullYear() â†’ year

getMonth() â†’ month (0â€“11)

getDate() â†’ day of month (1â€“31)

getDay() â†’ day of week (0 = Sunday)

getHours(), getMinutes(), getSeconds(), getMilliseconds()

getTime() â†’ timestamp (ms since 1970)

getTimezoneOffset() â†’ timezone difference in minutes

(There are also UTC versions: getUTCFullYear(), getUTCHours() etc.)

------------------------------------------------------------->

âœ… Setting Values

setFullYear(year, month?, day?)

setMonth(month, day?)

setDate(day)

setHours(h, m?, s?, ms?)

setMinutes(), setSeconds()

setTime(timestamp)

----------------------------------------------------------------->

âœ… Formatting Dates

.toDateString() â†’ "Sat Sep 06 2025"

.toISOString() â†’ "2025-09-06T10:30:00.000Z" (standard for APIs)

.toLocaleDateString("en-IN") â†’ "06/09/2025"

.toLocaleTimeString("en-US", { hour: "2-digit", minute: "2-digit" }) â†’ "10:30 AM"

.toString() â†’ full string with timezone

--------------------------------------------------------------------->

âœ… Useful Tricks in Projects

