ðŸš€ Most Used in Real Projects

Date.now() â†’ store timestamps

.toISOString() â†’ save in DB (MongoDB, SQL)

.toLocaleDateString() / .toLocaleTimeString() â†’ show user-friendly date/time

getFullYear, getMonth, getDate â†’ extract parts for reports/filters

Difference in dates (like subscription expiry, task deadline)

setDate(getDate() + n) â†’ add/subtract days


------------------------------------------------------------->


âš¡ Bonus: Libraries (very common in projects)


Because native Date is clunky, most projects use:

Moment.js (older, still used in many codebases)

Day.js (lightweight modern alternative)

date-fns (functional, tree-shakeable, very popular)

Luxon (powerful, timezone handling)

Example with date-fns:

import { format, addDays, differenceInDays } from "date-fns";

format(new Date(), "dd/MM/yyyy");         // 06/09/2025
addDays(new Date(), 7);                   // 1 week later
differenceInDays(new Date("2025-09-10"), new Date("2025-09-06")); // 4


